  "prompt": "What is the first day at KMC, Manipal like?",
  "response": "The first day at Kasturba Medical College (KMC) in Manipal, India typically involves orientation activities designed to familiarize new students with the college, its facilities, rules, and the overall academic environment. \n\n1. **Registration and Documentation:** Students usually complete their registration process, submit necessary documentation, and receive their student IDs.\n\n2. **Orientation Session:** There is likely an orientation session where faculty members and administrative staff introduce themselves and provide an overview of the curriculum, examination patterns, and other academic guidelines.\n\n3. **Campus Tour:** New students may be given a tour of the campus, showing them key locations such as lecture halls, laboratories, libraries, cafeterias, hostels, sports facilities, and other important buildings.\n\n4. **Meeting with Seniors and Faculty:** Opportunities to interact with senior students, faculty members, and student organizations might be arranged. This helps freshmen to get insights, advice, and guidance for the upcoming years.\n\n5. **Introduction to Extracurricular Activities:** Information about clubs, societies, and extracurricular activities available at KMC often forms part of the orientation to encourage a well-rounded college experience.\n\n6. **Introductory Lectures:** Sometimes, introductory lectures or talks on the first day set the tone for the academic rigor and expectations of medical studies.\n\nOverall, the first day is a mixture of administrative tasks, socializing, and receiving essential information to help students transition smoothly into their new academic life at KMC, Manipal.",
